{"article_id":"N4QCng4gyoMxPFUC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Trump signed an order Friday","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"expanding his travel ban to six new countries ,","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"targeting nations","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"the government says","depth":12},{"id":4,"text":"pose a threat","depth":12},{"id":5,"text":"because they don ' t issue electronic passports","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"or don ' t do enough","depth":12},{"id":7,"text":"to share information with American authorities","depth":13},{"id":8,"text":"to vet their citizens","depth":14},{"id":9,"text":"looking to travel .","depth":14},{"id":10,"text":"The six countries are Burma , Eritrea , Kyrgyzstan , Nigeria , Sudan and Tanzania .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"They join seven countries","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"who are still part of the president ' s previous travel ban :","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"Iran , Libya , North Korea , Somalia , Syria , Venezuela and Yemen .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"\" It is fundamental to national security , and the height of common sense ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"if a foreign nation wishes to receive the benefits of immigration and travel to the United States ,","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"it must satisfy basic security conditions","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"outlined by America ' s law-enforcement and intelligence professionals , \"","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"said White House press secretary Stephanie Grisham .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"Only immigrant applications from Burma , Eritrea , Kyrgyzstan and Nigeria will be blocked ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"while other travelers are not affected .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"For Sudan and Tanzania , only applicants under the diversity visa program will be blocked ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"a Homeland Security official said .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"That means businesses can still bring in temporary workers","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"and family members can still visit relatives here .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"The official said","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"the lower level of ban reflects the countries ' conditions .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"\" These six countries have a greater prospect","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"of making improvements , \"","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"the official said .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"The additional ban will take effect Feb. 22 ,","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"so nobody","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"traveling now","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"will be affected ,","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"nor will those","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"who already have visas .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Anyone already in the U.S. is unaffected , too .","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"Based on past trends ,","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Homeland Security said","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"perhaps 12,000 people would be affected by the expanded ban .","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"Immigrant-rights groups complained","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"that the expanded ban could harm vulnerable people .","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"\" We are particularly concerned about Burmese refugees","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"who may see America ' s doors closed to them at a time of desperate need","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"- including thousands of ethnic Chin , Karen , and Muslim Rohingya ,","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"who have fled severe persecution , \"","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"said Krish O ' Mara Vignarajah , president of Lutheran Immigration and Refugee Service","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"Mr. Trump issued his first travel ban Jan. 27 , 2017 , on seven majority-Muslim countries ,","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"virtually banning all entry of citizens from those countries .","depth":5},{"id":50,"text":"That derided as a \" Muslim ban , \"","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"and was halted by federal judges .","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"Mr. Trump would make two subsequent revisions","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"to narrow the ban","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"and alter the countries covered ,","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"deleting some of the original nations","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"and adding in two non-Muslim nations , North Korea and Venezuela .","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"The Supreme Court in 2018 ruled","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"that version of the ban was legal on its face","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"- though it left room for challenges on how the ban was carried out .","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"Those challenges are still making their way through lower courts .","depth":5},{"id":61,"text":"Homeland Security officials defended the new additions to the list ,","depth":3},{"id":62,"text":"saying","depth":4},{"id":63,"text":"they were added after an extensive review of every country ' s vulnerabilities and willingness","depth":5},{"id":64,"text":"to share information with the U.S.","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"so that their citizens","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"looking to travel to the U.S.","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"can be properly vetted .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"\" DHS and the Department of State have informed each of the six countries about their specific deficiencies , \"","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"a Homeland Security official said ,","depth":5},{"id":70,"text":"adding","depth":5},{"id":71,"text":"that countries can earn their way off the list","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"by improving their cooperation .","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"That happened in April 2018","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"when Chad made enough improvements","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"to be dropped from the travel ban ,","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"the official said .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":153,"left":137,"right":152,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":124,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":117,"right":123,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":107,"right":116,"relat